    skos:editorialNote "The ontology incorporates much of UFO-L, a legal core ontology (Griffo, 2018), and also to a lesser degree E-OPL, Enterprise Core Ontology (Falbo et al., 2014), and OntoCrime (Mário de Oliveira Rodrigues et al., 2020) (rodrigues2019ontocrime).";
